# Debugging and shell (agent)

## HTML / layout / browser behaviour

- Prefer **automated browser checks** over asking the user to open **DevTools** or manually inspect the DOM. The repo already has **Playwright** (`devDependency`) and scripts under `scripts/` (e.g. `debug-hero-dom.mjs`, `debug-hero-refresh-timeline.mjs` — see `package.json` `debug:*` scripts).
- When investigating stacking, CLS, scroll, or hydration timing, **add or extend a small Playwright script** (or run an existing one) and interpret the output yourself.
- Only ask the user to use DevTools or capture a recording when automation cannot reproduce the issue or you need **subjective** feedback (e.g. “does this feel janky?”).

## Terminal commands

- If a command is **safe to run in this environment** (build, lint, tests, `node` scripts, `npm run …`, starting a local server for probes), **run it yourself** — do not hand the user a list of commands unless there is a **good reason** (needs their secrets, destructive git, production DB, network they must approve, or their machine-only paths).
- If a command **fails** (permissions, missing env), try alternatives or report the error clearly; still avoid “please run X” when you can run X.
- **`npm run db:migrate`** — same rule: the agent runs it when `DATABASE_URL` / `DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED` is available (e.g. project `.env.local`). See **`database-migrations.mdc`** — do not default to asking the user to migrate locally.
